<h1>Study</h1>
<hr>
<p>
Abdominal Ultrasound<br>
-  Focus: Comprehensive training in diagnostic abdominal ultrasound.<br>
-  Curriculum: Physics of ultrasound, probe handling, abdominal organ imaging, artifact recognition, and clinical interpretation.<br>
-  Hands-on Training: Supervised scanning sessions with patients.<br>
-  Outcome: Competency in performing and interpreting abdominal ultrasound for clinical practice.<br>
<hr>
Endoscopy<br>
-  Focus: Practical and theoretical mastery of gastrointestinal endoscopy.<br>
-  Curriculum: Upper and lower GI endoscopy techniques, patient preparation, sedation protocols, complication management.<br>
-  Hands-on Training: Direct practice under expert supervision in clinical settings.<br>
-  Outcome: Ability to perform diagnostic and therapeutic endoscopic procedures safely.<br>
<hr>
Nutrition<br>
-  Focus: Clinical nutrition and dietetics for patient care.<br>
-  Curriculum: Nutritional assessment, therapeutic diets, metabolic disorders, and evidence-based dietary interventions.<br>
-  Hands-on Training: Case-based learning, patient counseling, and nutrition planning.<br>
-  Outcome: Expertise in integrating nutrition into clinical management.<br>
<hr>
Functional Medicine<br>
-  Focus: Systems-based approach to chronic disease management.<br>
-  Curriculum: Root-cause analysis, biochemical individuality, integrative diagnostics, and personalized treatment strategies.<br>
-  Hands-on Training: Clinical case discussions, protocol development, and patient-centered care.<br>
-  Outcome: Skills to apply functional medicine principles in clinical practice.<br>
<hr>
Lifestyle Medicine<br>
-  Focus: Evidence-based interventions for prevention and management of lifestyle-related diseases.<br>
-  Curriculum: Physical activity, stress management, sleep hygiene, behavioral change strategies.<br>
-  Hands-on Training: Patient workshops, counseling sessions, and community health projects.<br>
-  Outcome: Competence in promoting lifestyle modifications for long-term health.<br>
<hr>
Program Features<br>
-  Duration: 1 year<br>
-  Mode: Blended learning (classroom + clinical practice)<br>
-  Placement: Clinical placement opportunities provided<br>
-  Certification: Postgraduate skill development certificate upon completion<br>
These programs are designed to empower healthcare professionals with advanced skills, bridging the gap between theory and clinical application.
</p>
